questions.explanation:
&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;option 1) i.e.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;stale but it smelled&amp;nbsp;delicious so that&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;span id=&quot;docs-internal-guid-a346a455-7fff-aa7b-0250-2f7267f8c74a&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;  background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; text-decoration-line: underline; text-decoration-skip-ink: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;border:none;display:inline-block;overflow:hidden;width:48px;height:48px;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;48&quot; src=&quot;https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/qDYrZqa9bQUqkqd199gfPANHfRcCyQkM8h-0ZOtd9QHwrvsslsR9F6G7cO89FghVbGAuk5TsJDbMr1huLuv0e6odFTtNj5qoJ5mVG8VYUqBROHSt-qg1DnTryx3wYvenUgTzua4W&quot; style=&quot;margin-left:0px;margin-top:0px;&quot; width=&quot;48&quot; /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:20px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;  background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; text-decoration-line: underline; text-decoration-skip-ink: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;EXPLANATION&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;  background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; text-decoration-line: underline; text-decoration-skip-ink: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;  background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The verbs of sensation &lt;strong&gt;(seem, look, feel, appear, taste, sound and smell)&lt;/strong&gt; are&amp;nbsp;followed by &lt;strong&gt;adjective &lt;/strong&gt;not an adverb.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;In place of adverb &amp;#39;deliciously&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;we should use &amp;#39;delicious&amp;#39; which is an adjective.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Next, &lt;strong&gt;Staled &lt;/strong&gt;will be changed into &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;stale&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot; because stale is already an adjective and we can not add &amp;quot;ed&amp;quot; in&amp;nbsp;adjectives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;docs-internal-guid-948f7567-7fff-58cf-7d2e-555ef573bdb1&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;  background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;border:none;display:inline-block;overflow:hidden;width:20px;height:20px;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;20&quot; src=&quot;https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/ndX9JG3xc0xgziugYWSVlt6M0F2xlmciBTc3F2aOXA333mJKs1ybUhz0ooc80p688Tma3W5MIlLWWXRTAFIwzr60Xp4tRQT-vEICmHW9Qptr_-MNbeBZpagdWrAe76H8elpbEPLF&quot; style=&quot;margin-left:0px;margin-top:0px;&quot; width=&quot;20&quot; /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;Sentence after improvement: &lt;em&gt;Although the&amp;nbsp;food was &lt;strong&gt;stale &lt;/strong&gt;but it smelled&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;delicious&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;so that no one believed it was cooked yesterday.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;Water, which is a natural resource, has to be shared by all creations of God&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The instructions given below should be followed while changing an&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;assertive sentence to passive voice&lt;/span&gt;.

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Find the&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;subject and object&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;of the sentence and&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;exchange their places&lt;/span&gt;; make changes in their&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;cases&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;as well if subject and object are&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;pronouns&lt;/span&gt;.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Use preposition&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;#39;by&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;before the agent.&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;(by all creations of God)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Use an appropriate&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;helping verb&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;in&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;passive form&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;according to the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;tense of the active form&lt;/span&gt;.&amp;nbsp;
		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;have/has/had + to + V&lt;sub&gt;1&lt;/sub&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; changes to&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;have/has/had + to + be + V&lt;sub&gt;3&lt;/sub&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; You &lt;strong&gt;have to&lt;/strong&gt; complete the work. &lt;em&gt;(Active)&lt;/em&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
			&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;The work&lt;strong&gt; has to be &lt;/strong&gt;completed by you.&lt;em&gt; (Passive)&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;Here, &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;water&amp;#39; &lt;/strong&gt;takes the helping verb&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;has&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; as it is a &lt;strong&gt;singular noun&lt;/strong&gt;.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Always use the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;third form&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;of the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;main verb&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;in&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;passive form&lt;/span&gt;.&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;(Shared)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;At last, line up the remaining part.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Final sentence&lt;/u&gt;:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Water, which is a natural resource, has to be shared by all creations of God.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;https://storage.googleapis.com/tb-img/production/21/01/hin1.png&quot; style=&quot;font-weight: 700; width: 200px; height: 92px;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Passive voice&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;में&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;assertive sentence&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;को बदलते समय नीचे दिए गए निर्देशों का पालन किया जाना चाहिए।

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;वाक्य के&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;subject&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;और&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;object&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;का पता लगाएं और उनके स्थानों को बदले; यदि उनके&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;subject&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;और&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;object pronoun&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;हैं, तो उनके&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;cases&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;में भी बदलाव करें।&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Agent&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;से पहले&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;preposition &amp;#39;by&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;का उपयोग करें।&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;(by all creations of God) (&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;भगवान की सभी कृतियों द्वारा&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Active voice&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;के&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;tense&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;के अनुसार&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;passive voice&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;में एक उपयुक्त&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;helping verb&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;का उपयोग करें।&amp;nbsp;
		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;have/has/had + to + V&lt;span style=&quot;position: relative;  line-height: 0; vertical-align: baseline; bottom: -0.25em;font-size:10.5px;&quot;&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;बदलता है&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;#39;have/has/had + to + be + V&lt;span style=&quot;position: relative;  line-height: 0; vertical-align: baseline; bottom: -0.25em;font-size:10.5px;&quot;&gt;3&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;में.&lt;/li&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;उदाहरण:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;You&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;have to&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;complete the work.&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;(Active)&lt;/em&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
			&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; The work&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;has to be&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;completed by you.&lt;em&gt;&amp;nbsp;(Passive)&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;यहाँ,&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;water&amp;#39; &lt;/strong&gt;helping verb &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;has&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;को&amp;nbsp;लेता है क्योंकि यह एक&lt;strong&gt; singular noun&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;है।&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;हमेशा&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;main verb&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;के&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;third form&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;का प्रयोग&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;passive voice&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;में करें।&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;(Shared)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;अंत में, शेष भाग को व्यवस्थित करें।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

questions.statement:
&lt;p&gt;Change the given dialogue into reported speech.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Tina: Where are you going, son?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Son: Mom, I am going to my friend&amp;rsquo;s house to play.&lt;/p&gt;

questions.explanation:
&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Tina asked her son where he was going. He replied that he was going to his friend&amp;rsquo;s house to play.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;given sentence&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;is a&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;direct speech&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;basic rules&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;for changing or&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;converting direct speech into indirect speech:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;​&lt;/span&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;commas, inverted commas&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;are&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;removed&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The use of&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;: and ?&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;implies that Tina asked his son where he was going.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Son replied to mom that he was&amp;nbsp;going to his&amp;nbsp;friend&amp;rsquo;s house to play.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Now, in the first part i.e.&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Where are you going, son?&lt;/strong&gt;,&amp;nbsp;The pronoun &amp;#39;you&amp;#39; will be changed into &amp;#39;he&amp;#39; and &amp;quot;are&amp;quot; will be changed to &amp;quot;was&amp;quot; as past tense will be used instead of present tense.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Similarly in the second part i.e.&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Mom, I am going to my friend&amp;rsquo;s house to play,&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The pronoun &amp;#39;I&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39; will be changed into &amp;#39;he&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39; and&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&amp;quot;am&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&amp;quot; will be changed to &amp;quot;was&amp;quot; as past tense will be used instead of present tense.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Thus, the reported speech will be:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700; &quot;&gt;Tina asked her son where he was going. He replied that he was going to his friend&amp;rsquo;s house to play.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;Option 2&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The passage discusses how &lt;strong&gt;sensational reporting&lt;/strong&gt; may attract attention but can negatively influence how people understand news.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The sentence states that such reporting can create &lt;strong&gt;unnecessary panic&lt;/strong&gt;, which suggests a negative effect on how the public interprets information.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Distort&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; means to twist or misrepresent facts, giving a misleading impression. This fits perfectly with the idea of sensational news affecting public understanding.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Other options such as &lt;strong&gt;clarify, strengthen,&lt;/strong&gt; and &lt;strong&gt;validate&lt;/strong&gt; indicate positive or neutral effects, which do not match the negative context of sensational reporting.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;Option 2&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Clarify (स्पष्ट करना):&lt;/strong&gt; To make something clear or easier to understand. This does not fit because sensational reporting misleads rather than explains.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Strengthen (मजबूत करना):&lt;/strong&gt; To make something stronger or more effective. This contradicts the negative effect described in the sentence.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Validate (मान्य करना / सत्यापित करना):&lt;/strong&gt; To confirm or prove the truth of something. This meaning does not align with the misleading nature of sensational reporting.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;Option 3&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The passage discusses how misinformation spreads quickly when news organizations prioritize speed over accuracy.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The sentence states: &lt;em&gt;&amp;quot;When news outlets prioritize speed over accuracy, misinformation can (2) ______ rapidly across digital platforms.&amp;quot;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The verb &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;circulate&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; means to spread or move widely among people or platforms, which perfectly fits the context of misinformation spreading online.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Thus, &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;circulate&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; appropriately completes the sentence by indicating how misinformation spreads quickly through digital media.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;Option 3&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Decline (गिरावट / कम होना):&lt;/strong&gt; Means to decrease or become weaker. It does not fit the context of misinformation spreading across platforms.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hesitate (संकोच करना):&lt;/strong&gt; Means to pause or be uncertain before doing something. It is unrelated to the idea of information spreading.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Disappear (गायब हो जाना):&lt;/strong&gt; Means to vanish or cease to exist. This is opposite to the idea of misinformation spreading widely.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;influence&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The passage discusses the role of media in shaping public opinion and the ethical responsibilities of journalism.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The sentence states that advertisements and sponsorships may subtly ______ editorial priorities.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The word &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;influence&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; fits best because advertisements and sponsorships can affect or shape editorial decisions and content selection.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The other options do not logically fit the context since advertisements generally affect editorial priorities rather than ignore, eliminate, or prohibit them.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;Option 4&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ignore (अनदेखा करना):&lt;/strong&gt; to refuse to take notice of something.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Eliminate (समाप्त करना):&lt;/strong&gt; to completely remove or get rid of something.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Prohibit (प्रतिबंधित करना):&lt;/strong&gt; to formally forbid something by law or authority.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;Option 4&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The passage emphasizes the importance of &lt;strong&gt;media literacy&lt;/strong&gt; so that citizens can analyze news critically.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The sentence states that media literacy enables citizens to critically ______ news content rather than accepting it blindly.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Evaluate&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; means to carefully examine or assess something to form a judgment.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Thus, it correctly fits the context because citizens should &lt;strong&gt;critically assess or evaluate news content&lt;/strong&gt; instead of accepting it without questioning.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;Option 4&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Endorse&lt;/strong&gt; (समर्थन करना): To publicly support or approve something.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Promote&lt;/strong&gt; (प्रोत्साहित करना): To actively encourage or advertise something.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Replicate&lt;/strong&gt; (प्रतिलिपि बनाना): To copy or reproduce something.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;enhance&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The passage discusses the importance of &lt;strong&gt;ethical journalism&lt;/strong&gt; and how responsible media strengthens democratic dialogue.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The final sentence states that when media organizations follow principled standards, they build trust and support constructive debate.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Enhance&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; means to improve or increase the quality or value of something.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Thus, ethical journalism helps &lt;strong&gt;enhance public confidence&lt;/strong&gt;, which fits logically and contextually in the sentence.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Other options suggest weakening or reducing trust, which contradicts the positive outcome described in the passage.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;Option 1&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Erode (क्षीण करना):&lt;/strong&gt; It means to gradually weaken or destroy something. This does not fit the context because ethical journalism strengthens public confidence, not weakens it.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Compromise (समझौता करना / कमजोर करना):&lt;/strong&gt; It means to weaken or put something at risk. This contradicts the idea of responsible media building trust.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Diminish (कम करना):&lt;/strong&gt; It means to reduce or make something less important. This also does not suit the positive outcome described in the passage.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

questions.statement:
&lt;p&gt;Direction : In each of the following questions, there are six sentences marked S1, S, P, Q, R, S6. The positions of S1&amp;nbsp;and S6&amp;nbsp;are fixed. You are required to choose one of the four alternatives that would be the most logical sequence of the sentences in the passage.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;!-- x-tinymce/html --&gt;S1:&amp;nbsp;The coconuts are usually picked before they are quite ripe to stop them from falling to the ground or into the water.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;P: First, he fastens a strong piece of rope around his ankles; then he puts both hands around the smooth tree-trunk and grips it lower down with his bare feet.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Q: It is exciting to watch him climb.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;R: To pick them, a man climbs up the tree, taking with him only a very sharp knife and a little coil of rope.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;S: When he is ready to start, he gives a jerk and moves his feet higher up the trunks, then another jerk and moves his hands.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;S6 : Like this, in a series of jerks, first feet and then hands, he goes right to the top of the tree taking the rope with him.&lt;/p&gt;

questions.explanation:
&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;Option 4&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The paragraph begins by explaining how coconuts are picked before they are ripe to prevent damage.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sentence R is the first sentence&lt;/strong&gt; as it explains the method of picking coconuts:&lt;/span&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&amp;quot;To pick them, a man climbs up the tree, taking with him only a very sharp knife and a little coil of rope.&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sentence Q follows&lt;/strong&gt; as it describes how exciting it is to watch the climber:&lt;/span&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&amp;quot;It is exciting to watch him climb.&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sentence P is the third sentence&lt;/strong&gt; as it elaborates on the preparation for climbing:&lt;/span&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&amp;quot;First, he fastens a strong piece of rope around his ankles; then he puts both hands around the smooth tree-trunk and grips it lower down with his bare feet.&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sentence S is the fourth&lt;/strong&gt; as it explains the jerking motion used to climb:&lt;/span&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&amp;quot;When he is ready to start, he gives a jerk and moves his feet higher up the trunks, then another jerk and moves his hands.&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct sequence is &lt;strong&gt;RQPS&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Coherent paragraph after rearrangement&lt;/strong&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&amp;quot;To pick them, a man climbs up the tree, taking with him only a very sharp knife and a little coil of rope. It is exciting to watch him climb. First, he fastens a strong piece of rope around his ankles; then he puts both hands around the smooth tree-trunk and grips it lower down with his bare feet. When he is ready to start, he gives a jerk and moves his feet higher up the trunks, then another jerk and moves his hands.&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

questions.statement:
&lt;p&gt;Sentences of a paragraph are given below in jumbled order. Arrange the sentences in the correct order to form a meaningful and coherent paragraph.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A. During that time she would forget all her work and listen with the greatest concentration.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;B. Later, she could repeat the entire text by heart.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;C. My grandmother never went to school so she could not read.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;D. Every Wednesday, a magazine called Karmaveera would come, and I would read a story to her.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

questions.explanation:
&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&lt;strong&gt; &amp;quot;CDAB&amp;quot;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;C.&amp;quot; &lt;/strong&gt;starts with an important piece of information about the grandmother, establishing that she never went to school and couldn&amp;#39;t read.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;D.&amp;quot; &lt;/strong&gt;then provides context as to what happened given the grandmother&amp;#39;s situation. This reveals the connection between the narrator (most likely a grandchild) and the grandmother via a weekly ritual of story-telling from a magazine called Karmaveera.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;A.&amp;quot; &lt;/strong&gt;elaborates on the grandmother&amp;#39;s behavior during these story-telling sessions. It shows how engrossed she was in listening to the stories, indicating that she was learning and remembering them.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;B.&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; is the logical conclusion, showing the result of this weekly engagement: the grandmother, even though she couldn&amp;#39;t read, could repeat the entire text by heart after listening to it.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is&lt;strong&gt; &amp;quot;option 4&amp;quot;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Correct Paragraph:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&amp;quot;My grandmother never went to school so she could not read. Every Wednesday, a magazine called Karmaveera would come, and I would read a story to her. During that time she would forget all her work and listen with the greatest concentration. Later, she could repeat the entire text by heart.&amp;quot;&lt;/p&gt;
